          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "Text_Heading",
        "text": "5.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " And the name of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Jehiel",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is mentioned as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "of one with the king's sons",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "first",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " thing which may be observed as to this enumeration is that it is not one whole belonging to the later portion of David's time. Ahithophel had brag before put an end to his own life (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 17:21-23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; also see 2 Samuel 15:12, 31, 34; 16:20-23). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Secondly",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", that out of the seven names, four or five are already well known to us in some other capacity; for see the lists of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 18:14-17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 8:16-18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 20:23-26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". And ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "thirdly",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", that in one or two instances, a different or additional part is assigned to the names mentioned. The impression left with us is rather of honourable or special mention made of seven who had been distinguished helpers of the king or the kingdom at one time or another. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 32.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - Nothing is known of any ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "uncle",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " to David, named ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Jonathan",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but special mention is made, in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 20:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 21:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", of a nephew, son of Shimea, who rendered valuable service, and u-hose name was Jonathan. It is possible that the Hebrew ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "דּור",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " may mean \"nephew,\" as simply meaning \"relative.\" It must be admitted, however, as very remarkable, that in Leviticus, Numbers, the historical books, Jeremiah, and Amos, to the number of sixteen times in all, the word confessedly means \"uncle;\" while this seventeenth time, it would appear to mean \"nephew.\" On the other hand, in Proverbs, Canticles, Isaiah, Ezekiel, to the number of thirty-six times in all, the word follows its other branch of signification of \"love,\" and in particular \"one beloved.\" Nothing certain can be said of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Jehiel",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of this verse, but, if a son of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Hachmoni",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", we may presume him to have been related to Jashobeam of ver. 2 and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 11:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". 1 Chronicles 27:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
